briefTitle: Efficacy and Safety of the Biosimilar Ranibizumab FYB201 in Comparison to Lucentis in Patients With Neovascular Age-related Macular Degeneration
officialTitle: Efficacy and Safety of the Biosimilar Ranibizumab FYB201 in Comparison to Lucentis in Patients With Neovascular Age-related Macular Degeneration
summary: The purpose of this study is to determine the efficacy and safety of the biosimilar ranibizumab FYB201 in comparison to Lucentis in patients with neovascular age-related macular degeneration.

primaryOutcome.measure: Change From Baseline in Best Corrected Visual Acuity (BCVA) [Letters] After 8 Weeks
